@startuml Electricity Cost Analytics
!theme sketchy-outline
skinparam componentStyle rectangle

actor "Operations\nManager" as user
participant "FastAPI\nRouter" as api
participant "Cost\nCalculator" as cost
participant "Statistics\nModule" as stats
participant "Trend\nAnalyzer" as trend
database "InfluxDB/\nTimestream" as tsdb
participant "Flux Query\nLibrary" as flux
actor "BI Tools\n(Grafana/PowerBI)" as bi

== Cost Analytics ==

user -> api: GET /costs?facility=X&period=daily
api -> tsdb: Query metering data\n(via Repository)
tsdb --> api: Raw measurements
api -> cost: Compute cost metrics
cost -> cost: Apply tariffs &\ntime-of-use pricing
cost --> api: Per-period cost breakdown
api --> user: JSON response

== Statistical Summaries ==

user -> api: GET /stats?meter=Y&window=7d
api -> stats: Compute statistics
stats -> stats: Pandas aggregations\n(mean, peak, stddev)
stats --> api: Statistical summary
api --> user: JSON response

== Trend Analysis ==

user -> api: GET /trends?facility=X&range=30d
api -> trend: Analyze trends
trend -> trend: Rolling averages &\nanomaly detection
trend --> api: Trend data & forecasts
api --> user: JSON response

== BI Integration ==

bi -> api: GET /analytics\n(dashboard queries)
api -> flux: Build Flux queries
flux -> tsdb: Optimized time-series queries
tsdb --> flux: Aggregated results
flux --> api: Structured data
api --> bi: JSON response

@enduml
